AgriChain Nigeria Prototype

Overview

The AgriChain Nigeria prototype demonstrates how smallholder farmers can record farming activities and receive transparent community funding using Solana.

Core User Flow

Farmer Registration

A farmer creates a profile and registers a farm.

Farm Activity Records

The farmer records important milestones:

- Land preparation
- Planting
- Fertilizer application
- Weeding
- Harvesting

Each milestone can later be linked to on-chain records on Solana.

Community Funding

Supporters browse active farming projects and contribute funds.

Progress Tracking

Supporters can track project progress through farm updates and funding milestones.

